<div class="container mx-auto">
    <div class="hero min-h-screen bg-base-200 mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center hero-content">
            <div class="">
                <h1 class="mb-12 text-5xl font-bold mt-14">
                    Backcaster.app
                </h1>


                <p class="text-xl">As a maker do you lose enthusiasm for your projects? Dread looking at your Jira / Trello board? Hit a wall not knowing what to do next?</p>
                <br>
                <p class="text-xl">Your tools should help you not get in the way.</p>
                <br>
                <p class="text-lg">Backcaster does things a little differently. Start from your goal and work backwards. Providing tools for keeping projects on track, keep your goal at the front of your mind and nudges for when you get stuck! <br><br>(No signups, no payment, get started with 1-click)</p>


                <%= form_tag("/create-board", method: :post) %>
                    <input type="hidden" name="theme" value="<%= @theme %>">
                    <input class="btn btn-primary btn-lg milestone-submit my-10" type="submit" value="Get started âž¡"/>
                </form>

                <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-10">4 steps to improvement</h1>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 max-w-xl mx-auto">
                    <div><p class="text-2xl">1) Define your ultimate goal</p><p class="mb-6">(with templates to help get you started)</p><img class="item-center" src="/images/goals.png"></div>
                    <div><p class="text-2xl mt-6">2) Break down into milestones</p><p class="mb-6">(with guides for common tasks & auto Gantt chart generation)</p><img class="item-center" src="/images/milestones.png"></div>
                    <div><p class="text-2xl mt-6">3) Todos for each milestone</p><p class="mb-6">(with visual history of each change; highlights when tasks are at risk of not being
                        done)</p><img class="" src="/images/todos.png"></div>
                    <div><p class="text-2xl mt-6 mb-6">4) Set habits for repetitive tasks</p><img class="mx-auto" src="/images/habits.png"></div>
                </div>
                <br>
                <br>
                <p><a href="/backcast/2f5304da-da7e-4afa-9a7b-fe59a1fa628f?theme=<%= @theme %>" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary">example ðŸ”Ž  </a></p>


                <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12">What users are saying</h1>
                <br>
                <div class="card text-center shadow-xl">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h2 class="card-title"><q>It is very hard to define my startup in just a sentence. This forced
                            me to really articulate what we are doing.</q></h2>
                        <p> - Jonathan Sinclair</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-12">Benefits</h1>
                <ul class="w-full steps steps-vertical">
                    <li class="step step-primary">Eliminate noise, a simple interface surfacing only what is important.
                    </li>
                    <li class="step step-secondary">Todo lists that works. Don't let an endless todo list sap your
                        motivation. (have one for each milestone)
                    </li>
                    <li class="step step-accent">Build habits; set reminders for tasks that have no end goal, but need to
                        be done daily | weekly | monthly.
                    </li>
                    <li class="step step-error">Collaborate. Share your URL and you can have your whole team working together in minutes.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <br>
                <br>
                <br>
                <%= form_tag("/create-board", method: :post) %>
                    <input type="hidden" name="theme" value="<%= @theme %>">
                    <input class="btn btn-primary btn-lg milestone-submit mt-4" type="submit" value="Get started âž¡"/>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <br>
    </div>
</div>